Melrose Plc (MRO) , a U.K. investment
company focused on engineering firms, said it will use 321
million pounds ($502 million) of loans to help fund the
acquisition of gas and power meters provider  Elster Group SE. (ELT)   The financing includes term loans and a revolving credit
from the London-based companyâ€™s banks, according to a statement.  Melrose will also finance the $2.3 billion deal with a 1.2
billion-pound rights offer.  Barclays Plc, Commerzbank AG, HSBC Holdings Plc, JPMorgan
Chase & Co., Lloyds Banking Group Plc and Royal Bank of Scotland
Group Plc led lenders in a 750 million-pound loan financing
signed in 2008, according to data compiled by Bloomberg.  To contact the reporter on this story:
